            <fr:taxon>Corollary</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For any <fr:link href="jms-017Y.xml" title="Regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular language</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> there exists a number <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\ell >1]]></fr:tex> satisfying the <fr:link href="jms-018L.xml" title="The pumping property" addr="jms-018L" type="local">pumping property</fr:link> with respect to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7726</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6116</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6116.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>By <fr:link href="jms-018B.xml" title="Kleene’s theorem" addr="jms-018B" type="local">Kleene’s theorem</fr:link>, there exists some <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}=L]]></fr:tex>; the rest follows from <fr:link href="jms-018M.xml" title="The pumping lemma for DFAs" addr="jms-018M" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-018M" /></fr:link>.</fr:p>
